ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Each reading is carefully analyzed for its thesis, and these theses are compared before class, during which time we cover the main ideas, in a 3 hour discussion.
Exhaustive theoretical review. By the end of the class, you will have a command of the anthropological literature that frames the notions of development and conservation.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course contributed massively to my thinking about the development of urban space, and this development's relationship with power and economy.
This course was essential for my research and above all for my intellectual growth.
